<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-12-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="408" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                        <head>408. Telegram 1276 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d408fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                                611.93/12–1255. Confidential; Limited Distribution.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-12-12">December 12, 1955,
                                    noon</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d408-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d408-1"/>
                        <p>1276. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>. Department’s
                            1372.</p>
                        <p>No record Chinese Communists ever told this in talks. They been told
                            repeatedly acceptance U.S. renunciation force proposal not to involve
                            third parties. For example my October 8 statement introducing item and
                            paragraph 15 my 872, paragraph 13 my 1056.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1"><hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>